result.execSummary:
The defendant Caitlin Jo H Whiting was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Caitlin Jo H Whiting is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Caitlin Jo H Whiting was found guilty of Possession of Drug Paraphernalia. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:19 AM Defendant Caitlin Jo H Whiting in court.  Prosecuting attorney Lindsey Hirt in court for the State of Wisconsin. All parties have agreed that some may have the hearing conducted remotely. This hearing has met the statutory standards for video conferencing. Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. Court advises of right to an attorney. Prosecuting attorney moves to amend Count 2 to Possession of Drug Paraphernalia County Ordinance 13-102(c)(14), Wisconsin Statutes and will dismiss Count 1. Court approves amendment. No contest plea entered. The Court will dismiss Count 1. As to Count 2, the Court orders the following: $267.50 to be paid within 30 days; Civil Judgment for non-payment of fine.
